title: US releases photo of Chinese 'spy balloon' taken by pilot before it was shot down
description: The US government has released a photo of a suspected Chinese surveillance balloon taken from the cockpit of an American spy plane before the device was shot down.

title: President Biden's words of resolve echo as he leaves Europe but worrying developments loom
description: Joe Biden flies home confident that a well choreographed trip has combined words, pictures and diplomacy to project a message of strength, resolve and unity.

title: Rapper Nipsey Hussle's killer sentenced to at least 60 years in prison
description: A Los Angeles judge has sentenced the killer of rapper Nipsey Hussle to at least 60 years in prison.

title: A focus on Ukraine has left German armed forces 'bleeding out'
description: In a quiet suburb on the edge of Hamburg, we get a glimpse into a small part of Germany's war machine.

title: Patriotism and love for Putin at pro-war rally as 'liberated' children paraded in front of crowd
description: Hours before Vladimir Putin was even set to turn up, tens of thousands of people were streaming towards Moscow's Luzhniki stadium.

title: US will defend 'every inch of NATO' - as Moscow welcomes China's help in 'resolving' Ukraine war
description: Joe Biden has said the US will defend "literally ever inch of NATO" in the face of Russian aggression - as Moscow welcomed China having a more active role in "resolving" the Ukraine war.

title: Problem with Begum case is we only hear her side - as UK intelligence on her is classified
description: "Can I keep my mask on? I'm looking ugly today," Shamima Begum asked me when we met in north-east Syria just over a year ago.

title: Mercenary boss releases image of dead soldiers accusing Moscow of depriving them of ammo
description: Russian mercenary boss Yevgeny Prigozhin has shared an image of dozens of fighters who have been killed, blaming the Russian Ministry of Defence of deliberately depriving them of ammunition.

title: 'A funeral we'll look forward to': Victory for islanders as stolen skulls to be returned and reburied
description: Trinity College Dublin (TCD) has agreed to return 13 human skulls that were stolen from a remote Irish island in 1890, after a campaign by the islanders.

title: Ten Palestinians killed and dozens wounded after Israeli military raid
description: Ten Palestinians have been killed and more than 90 injured during an Israeli military raid in the West Bank city of Nablus.

title: 'Please go home!' Firm tells workers to down tools in effort to create better work-life balance
description: An IT company in India is sending staff a message telling them to "please go home" in an effort to improve their work-life balance.

title: Vladimir Putin hosts pro-war rally ahead of first anniversary of invasion of Ukraine
description: About 200,000 people have gathered in Moscow to hear Vladimir Putin speak at a pro-war rally ahead of the first anniversary of Russia's invasion of Ukraine.

title: Father of two sisters murdered in Pakistan 'honour killings' detained in Spain
description: The father of two sisters murdered in so-called "honour killings" in Pakistan has been detained in Spain.

title: 15 people flee The Escape cargo ship after engine room catches fire in Baltic Sea
description: Fifteen people have fled a Dutch-flagged container vessel in the middle of the sea after its engine room caught fire.

title: Watch live: President Putin's pro-war rally
Teacher stabbed to death by pupil in southwest France
description: A teacher has been stabbed to death by a pupil during a lesson at a school in southwest France, government officials have said.

title: Ukrainian amputee soldiers vow to return to battlefield
description: Dmytro Skomoroh is a council official turned volunteer soldier for whom this war has dealt a cruel blow.

title: Russian radio stations play out 'fake' air raid warning after 'hack'
description: An air raid alert played out across Russian radio stations was the result of a cyber attack, Kremlin officials have claimed.

title: Mysterious metal ball washes up on beach in Japan
description: A mysterious large, metal ball has washed up on a beach in Japan, baffling the authorities and residents.

title: Starbucks launches olive oil coffee in Italy - and it's coming to the UK next
description: Frappuccinos are passé and milk and two sugars is practically prehistoric - the next coffee trend involves olive oil and it's launching in Italy on Wednesday.

title: Biden administration proposes tougher rules on asylum at US-Mexico border
description: The United States could bar tens of thousands of migrants from arriving at the US-Mexico border under a proposed plan which would require some asylum seekers to book a meeting with US officials first.

title: 'Poisoned candy': North Korean state media urges rejection of foreign aid despite food shortages
description: North Korea's official newspaper has said the country should reject foreign aid - likening it to "poisoned candy" - despite deepening hardships and reported food shortages.
